$$
x_{11} = 1 + c_{1}u_{1}, ~~~x_{12} = - (1 + c_{2}u_{2}), ~~~ x_{22} = 1 + c_{2}u_{2}, ~~~ x_{21} = 0.
$$

From boundary conditions (\ref{news:2}) we obtain 
$$
x_{11} = \frac{\alpha_{1}}{\ell_{1}}, ~~~ x_{12} = \frac{\alpha_{2}}{\ell_{2}}, ~~~ x_{22} = \frac{\alpha_{3}}{\ell_{3}}.
$$

